Package utils.json.protocol

Interface ServerMessageAction<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActivePhaseBody, CardPlayedBody, CardSelectedBody, CardsYouGotNowBody, CheckPointReachedBody, CurrentCardsBody, CurrentPlayerBody, DrawDamageBody, EnergyBody, ErrorBody, GameFinishedBody, GameStartedBody, HelloClientBody, MovementBody, NotYourCardsBody, PlayerAddedBody, PlayerShootingBody, PlayerStatusBody, PlayerTurningBody, RebootBody, ReceivedChatBody, SelectionFinishedBody, ShuffleCodingBody, StartingPointTakenBody, TimerEndedBody, TimerStartedBody, WelcomeBody, YourCardsBody
    public interface ServerMessageAction<T>
    This interface is implemented by each class in utils.json.protocol that represents the message body of a specific JSONMessage. It only demands a function to be implemented that contains all the logic that should happen when a message with the respective message body was received by either the client or the server.
